## Priority Score: 6/10
**Severity: 2 (Minor)** · **Urgency: 4 (High)**
**Category: Performance** · **Phase: 2**

### Summary
Implement virtualization for long lists (100+ models, many news cards) to prevent performance degradation.

### Detailed Description
**Problem:** Rendering 100+ items at once causes:
- High memory usage
- Slow initial render
- Laggy scrolling
- Poor performance on low-end devices

**Solution:** Virtualization renders only visible items.

### Lists to Virtualize

#### 1. Model Selection Dropdown (SettingsTab)
- Potentially 100+ models
- Currently renders all at once
- Target: Render only ~10 visible items

#### 2. News Cards List (NewsTab)
- Can have 50+ cards after search
- Each card is complex (truncation, actions)
- Target: Render only visible cards

#### 3. History Tab Card List
- Grows over time
- Archive can have 100+ cards
- Target: Render only visible cards

### Implementation Plan

#### Option 1: react-window (Simpler)
```bash
npm install react-window
```

```tsx
// components/VirtualizedModelList.tsx
import { FixedSizeList } from 'react-window';

interface Model {
  id: string;
  name: string;
}

interface Props {
  models: Model[];
  onSelect: (model: Model) => void;
}

export default function VirtualizedModelList({ models, onSelect }: Props) {
  const Row = ({ index, style }: any) => (
    <div style={style} onClick={() => onSelect(models[index])}>
      {models[index].name}
    </div>
  );

  return (
    <FixedSizeList
      height={400}
      itemCount={models.length}
      itemSize={48}
      width="100%"
    >
      {Row}
    </FixedSizeList>
  );
}
```

#### Option 2: react-virtuoso (More Features)
```bash
npm install react-virtuoso
```

```tsx
// components/VirtualizedCardList.tsx
import { Virtuoso } from 'react-virtuoso';

export default function VirtualizedCardList({ cards }: { cards: NewsCard[] }) {
  return (
    <Virtuoso
      data={cards}
      itemContent={(index, card) => (
        <NewsCard key={card.id} {...card} />
      )}
      style={{ height: '600px' }}
    />
  );
}
```

### Expected Improvements

**Before Virtualization:**
- 100 models: 5s render time
- High memory: 150MB
- Janky scrolling: 30 FPS

**After Virtualization:**
- 100 models: <500ms render time (-90%)
- Low memory: 50MB (-67%)
- Smooth scrolling: 60 FPS (+100%)

### Fix Complexity
- **Complexity:** Medium (3-4 hours)
- **Team:** Frontend Engineer

### Action Items
- [ ] Choose virtualization library (react-window vs react-virtuoso)
- [ ] Install dependency
- [ ] Implement virtualization for model list in SettingsTab
- [ ] Implement virtualization for news cards in NewsTab
- [ ] Implement virtualization for history cards in HistoryTab
- [ ] Test scrolling performance with 100+ items
- [ ] Ensure keyboard navigation still works
- [ ] Test on mobile devices
- [ ] Benchmark memory usage before/after

**Expected Impact:** Performance: 7/10 → 7.5/10

**Source:** PQA Report 2025-10-16 - Phase 2

## Priority Score: 7/10
**Severity: 3 (Medium)** · **Urgency: 4 (High)**
**Category: Performance** · **Phase: 2**

### Summary
Analyze and optimize bundle size to improve page load time and Core Web Vitals scores.

### Detailed Description
Large bundle sizes lead to:
- Slow initial page load (poor FCP, LCP)
- High bandwidth usage for users
- Poor performance on slow networks
- Worse SEO rankings

**Target:** Reduce bundle size by **30%+**

### Implementation Plan

#### 1. Install Bundle Analyzer
```bash
npm install -D @next/bundle-analyzer
```

```javascript
// next.config.js
const withBundleAnalyzer = require('@next/bundle-analyzer')({
  enabled: process.env.ANALYZE === 'true',
});

module.exports = withBundleAnalyzer({
  // ... existing config
});
```

#### 2. Analyze Current Bundle
```bash
ANALYZE=true npm run build
```

#### 3. Optimization Strategies

**A. Code Splitting**
```typescript
// Already using dynamic imports, but can expand
const PolicyViewer = dynamic(() => import('@/components/PolicyViewer'), {
  ssr: false,
  loading: () => <LoadingSpinner />
});

const HistoryTab = dynamic(() => import('@/components/HistoryTab'), {
  ssr: false
});
```

**B. Tree Shaking (Remove Unused Code)**
```typescript
// Bad: Imports entire lucide-react library
import * as Icons from 'lucide-react';

// Good: Import only what you need
import { ChevronDown, Search, Moon } from 'lucide-react';
```

**C. Lazy Load Heavy Dependencies**
```typescript
// Load markdown parser only when needed
const renderMarkdown = async (text: string) => {
  const { marked } = await import('marked');
  return marked(text);
};
```

**D. Use Next.js Font Optimization**
```typescript
// app/layout.tsx
import { Inter } from 'next/font/google';

const inter = Inter({ 
  subsets: ['latin'],
  display: 'swap', // Improve FCP
  preload: true
});
```

**E. Optimize Dependencies**
- Replace heavy libraries with lighter alternatives
- Use ESM versions when available
- Remove unused dependencies

### Expected Improvements
| Metric | Before | After | Improvement |
|--------|--------|-------|-------------|
| Bundle Size | ~500KB | <350KB | -30% |
| FCP | 2.5s | <1.8s | -28% |
| LCP | 3.2s | <2.5s | -22% |
| TTI | 4.5s | <3.5s | -22% |

### Fix Complexity
- **Complexity:** Medium (3-5 hours)
- **Team:** Frontend Engineer

### Action Items
- [ ] Install and run bundle analyzer
- [ ] Identify top 10 largest dependencies
- [ ] Expand code splitting for large components
- [ ] Audit and optimize icon imports
- [ ] Lazy load heavy dependencies
- [ ] Optimize font loading
- [ ] Remove unused dependencies
- [ ] Add bundle size tracking to CI (warn if bundle grows >5%)
- [ ] Run Lighthouse and compare scores before/after

**Expected Impact:** Performance: 5/10 → 6/10

**Source:** PQA Report 2025-10-16 - Phase 2

## Priority Score: 6/10
**Severity: 2 (Minor)** · **Urgency: 4 (High)**
**Category: Testing** · **Phase: 2**

### Summary
Add visual regression tests to catch unintended UI changes and styling regressions.

### Detailed Description
Without visual regression tests:
- CSS changes can break layouts unnoticed
- Component styling regressions go undetected
- Manual visual testing is time-consuming
- Difficult to ensure consistent UI across browsers

### Implementation Plan

#### 1. Install Playwright with Screenshots
```bash
npm install -D @playwright/test
npx playwright install
```

#### 2. Create Visual Test Suite
```typescript
// e2e/visual/components.spec.ts
import { test, expect } from '@playwright/test';

test.describe('Visual Regression Tests', () => {
  test('NewsTab layout', async ({ page }) => {
    await page.goto('http://localhost:3000');
    await page.click('text=News');
    await page.waitForLoadState('networkidle');

    // Take screenshot
    await expect(page).toHaveScreenshot('news-tab.png', {
      fullPage: true,
      threshold: 0.2, // Allow 20% difference
    });
  });

  test('SettingsTab layout', async ({ page }) => {
    await page.goto('http://localhost:3000');
    await page.click('text=Settings');
    await page.waitForLoadState('networkidle');

    await expect(page).toHaveScreenshot('settings-tab.png');
  });

  test('PolicyViewer dark mode', async ({ page }) => {
    await page.goto('http://localhost:3000');
    await page.click('text=Policy');

    // Toggle dark mode
    await page.click('[aria-label="Toggle dark mode"]');
    await page.waitForTimeout(500); // Wait for transition

    await expect(page).toHaveScreenshot('policy-viewer-dark.png');
  });

  test('NewsCard component', async ({ page }) => {
    await page.goto('http://localhost:3000');
    await page.click('text=News');

    const card = page.locator('[data-testid="news-card"]').first();
    await expect(card).toHaveScreenshot('news-card.png');
  });

  test('Mobile responsive - NewsTab', async ({ page }) => {
    await page.setViewportSize({ width: 375, height: 667 }); // iPhone SE
    await page.goto('http://localhost:3000');
    await page.click('text=News');

    await expect(page).toHaveScreenshot('news-tab-mobile.png');
  });
});
```

#### 3. Add to CI Pipeline
```yaml
# .github/workflows/visual-regression.yml
name: Visual Regression

on: [pull_request]

jobs:
  visual-test:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - uses: actions/setup-node@v4
      - run: npm ci
      - run: npx playwright install --with-deps
      - run: npm run build
      - run: npm run test:visual

      # Upload visual diffs if tests fail
      - uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4
        if: failure()
        with:
          name: visual-diffs
          path: test-results/
```

### Alternative: Chromatic (Easier Setup)
```bash
npm install -D chromatic
npx chromatic --project-token=<your-token>
```

### Fix Complexity
- **Complexity:** Medium (3-4 hours)
- **Team:** QA Engineer / Frontend Engineer

### Action Items
- [ ] Choose tool (Playwright screenshots vs Chromatic)
- [ ] Set up visual regression testing framework
- [ ] Create baseline screenshots for all major views
- [ ] Write visual tests for all tabs (News, Settings, Policy, History)
- [ ] Write visual tests for components (NewsCard, etc.)
- [ ] Add mobile viewport tests
- [ ] Add dark mode visual tests
- [ ] Integrate visual tests into CI
- [ ] Set up visual diff review process
- [ ] Document how to update baselines

**Expected Impact:** Testing: 8/10 → 8.5/10

**Source:** PQA Report 2025-10-16 - Phase 2

## Priority Score: 7/10
**Severity: 3 (Medium)** · **Urgency: 4 (High)**
**Category: Testing** · **Phase: 2**

### Summary
Add integration tests for Zustand store and state management to ensure state updates work correctly.

### Detailed Description
The application currently has NO integration tests for:
- Zustand store actions and state updates
- State persistence (localStorage)
- State hydration on app load
- State synchronization across tabs

### Test Coverage Needed

#### 1. Settings Store
- Add/update API key
- Select model
- Update model parameters (temperature, maxTokens)
- Reset to defaults
- Persist to localStorage

#### 2. Keywords Store
- Add keyword
- Update keyword weight/enabled
- Delete keyword
- Bulk operations
- Persist to localStorage

#### 3. News Store
- Store search results
- Update card status (archived, etc.)
- Filter/sort cards
- Persist to localStorage

### Implementation Plan
```typescript
// __tests__/integration/store.test.ts
import { renderHook, act } from '@testing-library/react';
import { useSettingsStore } from '@/lib/store';

describe('Settings Store Integration', () => {
  beforeEach(() => {
    localStorage.clear();
  });

  it('should persist API key to localStorage', () => {
    const { result } = renderHook(() => useSettingsStore());

    act(() => {
      result.current.setApiKey('test-api-key-123');
    });

    expect(result.current.apiKey).toBe('test-api-key-123');
    expect(localStorage.getItem('settings-storage')).toContain('test-api-key-123');
  });

  it('should hydrate state from localStorage', () => {
    // Pre-populate localStorage
    localStorage.setItem('settings-storage', JSON.stringify({
      state: { apiKey: 'persisted-key' }
    }));

    const { result } = renderHook(() => useSettingsStore());

    expect(result.current.apiKey).toBe('persisted-key');
  });

  it('should update model parameters', () => {
    const { result } = renderHook(() => useSettingsStore());

    act(() => {
      result.current.updateModelParams({
        temperature: 0.8,
        max_tokens: 2000
      });
    });

    expect(result.current.modelParams.temperature).toBe(0.8);
    expect(result.current.modelParams.max_tokens).toBe(2000);
  });
});
```

