## Priority Score: 7/10
**Severity: 3 (Medium)** · **Urgency: 4 (High)**
**Category: Security** · **Phase: 2**

### Summary
Configure CORS (Cross-Origin Resource Sharing) properly to prevent unauthorized cross-origin requests.

### Detailed Description
Without proper CORS configuration:
- Any website can call your API endpoints
- Data can be leaked to malicious sites
- CSRF attacks are easier to execute
- No control over who accesses your API

### Implementation Plan

#### Option 1: Next.js API Routes (if using)
```typescript
// lib/cors.ts
import { NextApiRequest, NextApiResponse } from 'next';

const allowedOrigins = [
  process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL,
  'http://localhost:3000',
  'https://yourdomain.com'
];

export function cors(req: NextApiRequest, res: NextApiResponse) {
  const origin = req.headers.origin;

  if (origin && allowedOrigins.includes(origin)) {
    res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Origin', origin);
    res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Methods', 'GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, OPTIONS');
    res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Headers', 'Content-Type, Authorization');
    res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Credentials', 'true');
  }

  if (req.method === 'OPTIONS') {
    res.status(200).end();
    return true;
  }

  return false;
}
```

#### Option 2: Next.js Middleware
```typescript
// middleware.ts
import { NextResponse } from 'next/server';
import type { NextRequest } from 'next/server';

export function middleware(request: NextRequest) {
  const origin = request.headers.get('origin');
  const response = NextResponse.next();

  if (origin && allowedOrigins.includes(origin)) {
    response.headers.set('Access-Control-Allow-Origin', origin);
    response.headers.set('Access-Control-Allow-Methods', 'GET, POST, OPTIONS');
    response.headers.set('Access-Control-Allow-Headers', 'Content-Type');
  }

  return response;
}

export const config = {
  matcher: '/api/:path*',
};
```

### Fix Complexity
- **Complexity:** Small (1-2 hours)
- **Team:** Backend Engineer

### Action Items
- [ ] Identify all API routes that need CORS
- [ ] Create `lib/cors.ts` utility
- [ ] Add CORS middleware to all API routes
- [ ] Whitelist production domains
- [ ] Test CORS with cross-origin requests
- [ ] Add CORS tests
- [ ] Document CORS configuration

**Expected Impact:** Security: 7/10 → 7.5/10

**Source:** PQA Report 2025-10-16 - Phase 2

## Priority Score: 7/10
**Severity: 3 (Medium)** · **Urgency: 4 (High)**
**Category: Security** · **Phase: 2**

### Summary
Implement a strict Content Security Policy to prevent XSS, code injection, and other content-based attacks.

### Detailed Description
Without CSP:
- **XSS Attacks:** Malicious scripts can execute
- **Code Injection:** Attackers can inject inline scripts
- **Data Theft:** Scripts can exfiltrate data to external domains
- **Clickjacking:** Frames can embed your site

### Recommended CSP Configuration

#### Phase 1: Report-Only (Test)
```typescript
// next.config.js
const ContentSecurityPolicy = `
  default-src 'self';
  script-src 'self' 'unsafe-eval' 'unsafe-inline';
  style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' https://fonts.googleapis.com;
  font-src 'self' https://fonts.gstatic.com;
  img-src 'self' data: https:;
  connect-src 'self' https://openrouter.ai;
  frame-ancestors 'none';
  base-uri 'self';
  form-action 'self';
`;

module.exports = {
  async headers() {
    return [
      {
        source: '/:path*',
        headers: [
          {
            key: 'Content-Security-Policy-Report-Only',
            value: ContentSecurityPolicy.replace(/\s{2,}/g, ' ').trim()
          }
        ]
      }
    ];
  }
};
```

#### Phase 2: Enforce (After Testing)
Change `Content-Security-Policy-Report-Only` to `Content-Security-Policy`

### Migration Strategy
1. **Week 1:** Deploy CSP in report-only mode
2. **Week 2:** Monitor violations, adjust policy
3. **Week 3:** Remove `unsafe-inline` and `unsafe-eval` (refactor code if needed)
4. **Week 4:** Switch to enforcement mode

### Fix Complexity
- **Complexity:** Medium (3-5 hours + monitoring)
- **Team:** Security Engineer / Frontend Lead

### Action Items
- [ ] Add CSP header in report-only mode
- [ ] Set up CSP violation reporting endpoint
- [ ] Monitor violations for 1 week
- [ ] Refactor inline scripts to external files
- [ ] Add nonces for necessary inline scripts
- [ ] Remove `unsafe-inline` and `unsafe-eval`
- [ ] Switch to enforcement mode
- [ ] Test all features work with strict CSP

**Expected Impact:** Security: 7.5/10 → 8/10

**Source:** PQA Report 2025-10-16 - Phase 2
